lmpton (Devon), or Broadwindsor and Little Windsor (Dorset). All these places have the same linguistic origin, whose meaning is controversial, but seems to be ‘windlass bank’ (Old English <i>windels</i> + <i>ōra</i>).","in Yorkshire perhaps a habitational name from Winds Over in Middleton (near Ilkley, Yorkshire). The placename probably derives from Old English <i>wind</i> ‘wind’ (genitive <i>windes</i>) + <i>ofer</i> ‘slope, hill, ridge’."],"variants":[{"name":"Winzer","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Gerhard, Ilse, Ingo, Wilhelm.","German: occupational name for a vine-grower or vintner, Middle High German <i>winzer</i>.","German: habitational name from any of various places so named in Bavaria."]},{"name":"Winsor","meanings":["English: variant of   Windsor  . This is the spelling used for places so named in Devon and Hampshire.","Perhaps also an Americanized form of German   Winzer  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Windsor was born about 1125, in Devon, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Hugh de Windsor. She had at least 1 son with William De Cogan."},"et":{"Abt 1125–":"umbes 1125–Surnud","1125–Female":"1125–Surnud","1145–1205":"1145–1205","1118–1201":"1118–1201","1164–1238":"1164–1238","1101–Male":"1101–Surnud","1118":"1118","1238":"1238","1205":"1205","1125":"1125","1201":"1201","1101":"1101","1145":"1145","1164":"1164","Abt 1125":"umbes 1125","Cogan, Glamorgan, Wales":"Cogan, Glamorgan, Wales","Cogan, Devon, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1125–":"noin 1125–Kuollut","1125–Female":"1125–Kuollut","1145–1205":"1145–1205","1118–1201":"1118–1201","1164–1238":"1164–1238","1101–Male":"1101–Kuollut","1118":"1118","1238":"1238","1205":"1205","1125":"1125","1201":"1201","1101":"1101","1145":"1145","1164":"1164","Abt 1125":"noin 1125","Cogan, Glamorgan, Wales":"Cogan, Glamorgan, Wales","Cogan, Devon, England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1125–":"environ 1125–Décédée","1125–Female":"1125–Décédée","1145–1205":"1145–1205","1118–1201":"1118–1201","1164–1238":"1164–1238","1101–Male":"1101–Décédé","1118":"1118","1238":"1238","1205":"1205","1125":"1125","1201":"1201","1101":"1101","1145":"1145","1164":"1164","Abt 1125":"environ 1125","Cogan, Glamorgan, Wales":"Cogan, Glamorgan, Galles","Cogan, Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Windsor est née environ 1125, à Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fille de Hugh de Windsor. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec William De Cogan."},"de":{"Abt 1125–":"um 1125–Verstorben","1125–Female":"1125–Verstorben","1145–1205":"1145–1205","1118–1201":"1118–1201","1164–1238":"1164–1238","1101–Male":"1